Quote:  A mammal-proof fence around an 18-ha enclosure was built by the Department of Conservation near Macraes Flat in eastern North Otago, to protect remnant populations of the critically endangered grand skink (<i>Oligosoma grande</i>) and Otago skink (<i>Oligosoma otagense</i>) (Reardon 2006).
Notes:  http://www.newzealandecology.org/nzje/

Date:  0/9/2009
Source:  NZ Geographic
Author:
Vol / Page:  99/18
Edition:
Quote:

Quote When the Great Otago Skink Recovery Programme began at Macraes Flat in 2004, the populations of Otago and grand skinks - New Zealand's largest and rarest lizards - were so low it was thought both species would be functionally extinct within the decade.
